vnalpha Debian package install and upgrade
===========================================

This package installs the host-native vnalpha CLI/TUI, an offline Python venv,
verification/startup/backup/restore helpers, and disabled-by-default daily
maintenance units. It does not install Docker Engine, credentials, a
vnstock-service image or the external /opt/openstock Compose deployment.

Install and initialize:

  sudo apt install -y ./vnalpha_<version>_amd64.deb
  sudo usermod -aG openstock "$USER"
  # Start a new login session, then:
  vnalpha init
  openstock-verify --mvp1

The timer remains disabled until explicitly enabled:

  sudo systemctl enable --now openstock-daily-pipeline.timer

Upgrades are offline and transactional. A replacement venv is built from the
bundled wheelhouse with --no-index and must pass a CLI smoke test before the
active venv is replaced. A missing or incomplete wheel bundle fails closed.

Research state is preserved under:

  /var/lib/openstock/warehouse
  /var/lib/openstock/knowledge
  /var/log/openstock

These paths use root:openstock ownership and group-write permissions. The daily
service runs as root with primary group openstock and UMask=0007.

FiinQuantX and LLM credentials remain disabled/empty by default. The installer
never enables commercial approvals or scheduled execution automatically.

See /usr/share/doc/vnalpha/OPERATOR.md for the complete operating guide.
